t\u00f3ria F.C.|Vit\u00f3ria Set\u00fabal]] | caps6 = 4 | goals6 = 0\n | years7 = 2005\u20132006 | clubs7 = [[Vit\u00f3ria F.C.|Vit\u00f3ria Set\u00fabal B]] | caps7 = 20 | goals7 = 2\n | years8 = 2007\u20132008 | clubs8 = [[Gela Calcio|Gela]] | caps8 = 5 | goals8 = 0\n | years9 = 2008\u20132009 | clubs9 = [[FC Gloria Buz\u0103u|Gloria Buz\u0103u]] | caps9 = 7 | goals9 = 0\n | years10 = 2009\u20132010 | clubs10 = [[Riffa S.C.|Al-Riffa]] | caps10 = \u2013 | goals10 = \u2013\n | years11 = 2011\u20132013 | clubs11 = [[Louletano D.C.|Louletano]] | caps11 = 20 | goals11 = 2\n | totalcaps = 101 | totalgoals = 6\n | nationalyears1 = 2003 | nationalteam1 = [[Portugal national under-19 football team|Portugal U19]] | nationalcaps1 = 2 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n | manageryears1 = 2018\u2013 | managerclubs1 = [[Amora F.C.|Amora]]\n}}\n\n'''Pedro Miguel Bra\u00e7o Forte Russiano''' (born 19 November 1984), simply known as '''Pedro Russiano''' is a [[Portugal|Portuguese]] former [[Association football|footballer]] and current [[Manager (association football)|manager]] at [[Amora F.C.|Amora]].\n\nRussiano was part of the [[Vit\u00f3ria F.C.|Vit\u00f3ria Set\u00fabal]] side who reached the [[2005\u201306 Ta\u00e7a de Portugal]].<ref>{{cite news|title=FC Porto 1-0 V. Set\u00fabal|trans-title=|url=http://www.zerozero.pt/jogo.php?id=221493|language=Portuguese|work=ZeroZero|date=|accessdate=31 October 2013}}</ref>\n\nAfter several unsuccessful seasons playing in Portugal, Russiano left for Italian club [[Gela Calcio]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gelacalcio.it/dettaglio.asp?id=1485 |title=COMUNICATO STAMPA 09 Agosto 2007 |date=9 August 2007 |accessdate=30 October 2010 |work=Gela Calcio |language=Italian |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716145708/http://www.gelacalcio.it/dettaglio.asp?id=1485 |archivedate=July 16, 2011 }}</ref> He would remain with the Italian side for one season after only five appearances.<ref>{{cite news|title=RUSSIANO PEDRO MIGUEL FONTE|t